# Server Actions Standard

## Action client

Always import from `@workspace/safe-action`. Never define
`createSafeActionClient()` in an app. Never copy `authActionClient` into an
app-local file.

## Schema method

Use `.inputSchema()`. This is next-safe-action v8 API. `.schema()` is v7 API and
must not be used.

## Revalidation

Call `revalidatePath()` inside the action body after every successful write. Use
`"layout"` when the full section tree must revalidate:

```ts
revalidatePath("/[locale]/(workspace)/(settings)/preferences", "layout")
```

Never call `router.refresh()` from a client component when a Server Action is
the mutation transport. `revalidatePath()` handles RSC invalidation server-side.

## Error handling

Do not throw inside action bodies. Return typed error states or use
`returnValidationErrors()` from `next-safe-action` for field-level errors. The
adapter automatically maps these to RHF `FieldErrors`.

## File naming and location

Server Action files are named `*.action.ts`. They live in an `_actions/`
directory inside the route segment that uses them. They are not shared across
routes. If two routes need the same write logic, that logic belongs in a shared
server-side helper in `@workspace/supabase-data`.

## Insert-or-update

The insert-or-update decision belongs inside the Server Action body. It uses
`ctx.userId` to check for an existing record and branches accordingly. Client
form islands never know which path was taken.
